<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101796114169338></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101796114169338><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101796114169338>Stat discussion</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101796114169338#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60483><span id=Scholar>Polyflame</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>18 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 4th 6:03 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi, I know this has been done a million times, but I just feel the urge to discuss it again.<br><br>Strength:&nbsp;&nbsp;I think this is the most important stat for a monk.  Even more important than stamina and agility.  Monks are a damage dealing class.  Strength lets you hit more and do more damage.<br>Dexterity:  This is an okay stat in my opinion.  It lets you proc more with weapons and you learn weapon skills quicker.  But there really are not very many good monk weapons with procs, exept for the suicide stick and celestial fists.  Besides, you can learn weapon skills quickly enough without the extra dexterity.<br>Stamina:  Even though most monks on this site put 20 points into it, I really don't see the point at all.  Monks are a damage dealing class, not a tank class.  Leave tanking to the warrs and hybrids, but we do the most melee damage out of any class.  Exept of course for rogue's backstab.  Besides, even if you put all 20 points into Stamina, it doesn't make much difference to your melee performance.  Sure, you won't suffer penalties for having your yellow bar depleted, but how often does that happen?  Never for a monk who is weight wise.  And at level 60, 1 point of stamina gives 4 hp.  That's it, 4 tiny little hp, so 20 points x 4 hp = 80 extra hp at level 60.  Woopie, it will only take about 1 more hit to kill you.  Big deal.  In my opinion, stamina is useless for a monk.<br>Agility:  This is an okay stat.  It lets you have a higher armor class, and it lets you dodge/block/riposte more often.  The problem is though, that it takes so many agility points to get even 1 point in ac.  So it's really not worth the trouble.<br>Intelligence:  This makes your general skills increase more quickly, but anyone can do that with practice and patience.  Besides, monks don't have an ounce of mana.  This is a useless stat for a monk.<br>Wisdom:  Another useless stat for a monk.  Sure, it may help with tailoring yourself some raw silk armor in low levels, but that's really about it.  Leave the trade skills to enchanters and priests.<br>Charisma:  This really has no benefit to the monk abilities.  The only benefit from charisma for a monk is cheaper prices from merchants.  So this would be another useless stat for a monk.<br><br>Okie dokey, that's my analysis on ideal stats for a monk.  What do you guys think of it?<br>&nbsp;<br>~Sloree<br>Nameless server<br>Level 46 Human Monk</td></tr>
