<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101798776071335></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101798776071335><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101798776071335>RE: Stat discussion</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101798776071335#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85748><span id=Guru>Uniero</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>62 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 5th 1:27 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.86]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My point about stamina is not that strength is not important.&nbsp;&nbsp;The issue is that there is a lot more str gear at lower levels than stamina.  It is important to get stamina over 100 if you use heavy weapons (2HB mostly) because if your stamina bar runs out you don't get penalties.  80 hp can make a huge difference in a fight.  Strength is important in my opinon, but defintely behind stamina.  I concur dex has its uses in procs, and agility is not all it is cracked up to be. Agility DOES NOT allow you to use your evade skills more, but may allow your to train the skills faster.  If you use a ratio of about 8 hp = 1 AC you can start comparing gear to see what is best for you.  Stamina falls into this according to your level. <br>Having said all of this I am convinced you could put all of your points into cha in the beginning and still have a great monk.  The game is designed to allow you to add points to stats as you go along.  Remember that no stat is worth AC when it comes down to it. <br><br><br>Uniero<br>45 Human Monk<br>Office Odin's Ghost<br>7th Hammer<br>(Oh where oh where has my little Raster gone, oh where oh where can he be?.....64 PH and counting)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
