	   <tr><td colspan=2>Amen! At my current level (24) I have been able to easily get gear that raises my str from it's base of 85 all the way up to 111, while it has been a struggle to get my sta from 95 to 100. <br><br>I created my monk after researching the suggested starting stats on this board. It has been stated that you can pretty much put your points wherever you want them and still have a good monk. I believe that's true, but I wanted as much of an advantage as I could get so I put all but 5 of my points into stamina, the other 5 went into str. Looking at how easy it's been to raise str I am now wishing I had put those additional 5 points into stamina. <br><br>One other point that has been raised is that at level 60, you gain 4 hps per point that you raise your stamina. I've seen this used as an argument against putting points into stamina, but don't you gain additional hps each level based on your base stamina? In other words, if you start 2 characters of identical class, one with 80 stamina, one with 100 stamina, take them both up to around level 30, strip them down, won't the one with 100 stamina have significantly higher hp's? I will admit that I haven't researched this, but the question just occurred to me while writing this post, so I apologize in advance if it has already been covered elsewhere. If one of you could point me to the post, or briefly answer my question here, that would be great.<br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 53 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
