	   <tr><td colspan=2>Personally, I find sneak has been one of the best solo skills especially combined with FD to allow you to bandage up. Not to mention you might need it to retrieve your corpse or just scout an area. Sneak is a very difficult skill to like at first because of the speed, and you really have to experiment to find out to use it best, but you can practise it while sitting and healing, chatting with friends, waiting for transport, or just about any time so it is actually one of the quickest skills to develop.<br><br>I definitely agree that in certain areas ID is awesome, and even better when you have a druid or ranger for SoW and to snare the mob for some heavy reverse-kite butt kicking. However, never use ID in a dungeon or it becomes Instill Train requiring a quick FD and sneaking out.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Apr&nbsp;&nbsp;4 12:01:39 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
