<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101778596529360></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101778596529360><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101778596529360>RE: 2hb vs dual wield weapons</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101778596529360#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>590 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 2nd 5:19 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The damage bonus does not add to the damage multiplier.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is extra damage added to every successful hit.  The disease damage, from my admittedly limited understanding, DOES add to the damage multiplier, but only against specific mobs, and it has a chance to be partially resisted.  In other words, against particular mobs, your damage multiplier can range from 30 to 37.<br><br>Speed is still basically irrelevant at your level.  KD is a better primary than CoT till you get to your 40s.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
