	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree! I have a lvl 33 ranger that has been collecting this stuff to sell and giving the extras to my lvl 15 monk. Here is a list of what I consider to be the best spore pieces for a monk, along with the prices that I sell them for in EC on Tholuxe Paells:<br><br>Spore Covered Hood&nbsp;&nbsp;     AC6 Int +1 20pp<br>Spore Covered Wristbands AC5 Sta +1 20pp<br>Spore Covered Sleeves    AC6 SvMagic +2 20pp<br>Spore Covered Tunic      AC12 Str +3 50pp<br>Spore Covered Boots      AC6 Agi +1 20pp<br>Spore Covered Leggings   AC7 SvCold +2 30pp<br>Weight on all pieces is 0.4<br>Total Weight -          2.4<br>Total AC -             42<br>Total Cost -          160pp<br>Stats raised - Int, Sta, SvMagic, Str, Agi, SvCold<br><br>Compare to the same Wu's pieces:<br>Wu's Fighting Cap        AC5 Agi +3 25pp<br>Wu's Fighting Wristbands AC4 Agi +1 25pp<br>Wu's Fighting Sleeves    AC5 Agi +3 25pp<br>Wu's Fighting Shirt      AC9 Agi +4 25pp<br>Wu's Fighting Slippers   AC5 Agi +2 25pp<br>Wu's Fighting Pantaloons AC6 Agi +4 25pp<br>Weight on all pieces is 0.10<br>Total Weight -          0.60<br>Total AC -             34<br>Total Cost -          150pp<br>Stat raised - Agi +17 (this would equate to about another 3 AC, bringing total AC up to 37)<br>The price on the Wu's is from a guy I found in FP who sells all Wu's items for 25pp, regardless of what they are. <br><br>So, for about an extra 10pp and 1.8 in weight you can increase your AC by 8. You will lose 16 on agility which equates to about another 3AC on the Wu's, but you gain Str, Sta, and a couple of saves. In my book, it is well worth the cost, plus it is stuff that anyone in their mid 20's can acquire without having to spend a lot of money on increasing their tailoring skill. <br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Apr  3 13:52:40 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 53 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_vi